OL,3,CWill Makerfield choose the next PM?
OL,5,FIn a video posted to X just after the
OL,6,Fpolls opened, Burnham said: "This is a
OL,7,Fchange by-election.
OL,9,F"We left Westminster 10 years ago to
OL,10,Fbuild something different, something
OL,11,Fbetter.
OL,13,F"We worked on a place-first basis,
OL,14,Frather than party first, problem
OL,15,Fsolving rather than point scoring.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/9
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,365,360,120,260,000,100
PN,36406
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F364A1781849901
OL,3,CWill Makerfield choose the next PM?
OL,5,F"We've taken that fight for people
OL,6,Fhere, and I'll carry that fight
OL,7,Fforward if I am lucky enough to be
OL,8,Felected as the MP for Makerfield. I'll
OL,9,Ftake that fight as high as I can
OL,10,Fpossibly take it."
OL,12,FStarmer has insisted he will not set
OL,13,Fout a timetable for his departure even
OL,14,Fif the Greater Manchester Mayor
OL,15,Freturns to parliament.
OL,17,FIf the PM does not resign, Burnham
OL,18,Fwould need to secure the backing of 81
OL,19,FLabour MPs to mount a leadership
OL,20,Fchallenge.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/9
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
