OL,3,CWill Makerfield choose the next PM?
OL,5,FIn Wigan, which includes part of
OL,6,FMakerfield, Labour lost all 22 of its
OL,7,Fcouncillors in the local election,
OL,8,Fwith Reform picking up 24 of the 25
OL,9,Fseats up for grabs.
OL,11,FIn the eight Makerfield wards that
OL,12,Fvoted in the local election, Reform
OL,13,Fsecured 50% of the vote while Labour
OL,14,Fgot 23%.
OL,16,FThere is however some suggestion
OL,17,FReform UK is losing voters to Restore
OL,18,FBritain, a party with a more hard-line
OL,19,Fapproach to migration and other issues.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G8/9
